    <!-- Heading Section -->
    <p class="absolute inset-0 flex justify-center items-center px-4 text-center text-white font-bold text-lg top-2/3 transform -translate-y-2/3 md:top-3/4 md:text-xl md:px-10 lg:text-4xl">
      Mufti Abdul Wahab Pakistan Relief Trip For Al-Wahab Foundation An Overview!
    </p>
    
    <!-- Date Section -->
    <div class="flex absolute inset-x-0 bottom-5 justify-center items-center text-white md:bottom-[12%]">
      <svg 
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
        class="stroke-customBeige w-5 h-5 md:w-6 md:h-6 lg:w-8 lg:h-8" 
        viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
        fill="none" 
        stroke="currentColor" 
        stroke-width="2" 
        stroke-linecap="round" 
        stroke-linejoin="round"
      >
        <path d="M8 2v4"/>
        <path d="M16 2v4"/>
        <rect width="18" height="18" x="3" y="4" rx="2"/>
        <path d="M3 10h18"/>
        <path d="M8 14h.01"/>
        <path d="M12 14h.01"/>
        <path d="M16 14h.01"/>
        <path d="M8 18h.01"/>
        <path d="M12 18h.01"/>
        <path d="M16 18h.01"/>
      </svg>
      <p class="mx-2 text-xs font-medium sm:text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg">
        November 15, 2024
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  

<div class="container">
    <div class="row px-4 md:px-20 my-10">
        <p class="text-grey text-base">
          Like every year, Chairman Al-Wahab Foundation, Mufti Abdul Wahab recently embarked on a journey to provide relief
          and hope in Pakistan with a focus on bringing assistance to underserved communities through various projects.
          Here’s an overview of his impactful Pakistan Relief Trip and humanitarian efforts done there.
        </p> 
    </div>
    <div class="md:px-20 px-4">
        <img class="w-full  h-full" src="https://alwahabfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/mufti-abdul-wahab-eye-care.jpg.webp" alt="" srcset="">
        <p class="text-maroon font-bold text-xl md:text-3xl my-4">Eye Surgery Camp at Al-Baseer Hospital, Karachi</p>
        <p>Chairman Mufti Abdul Wahab began his journey by visiting Al-Baseer Hospital in Karachi, where he met with eye surgery patients. Al-Wahab Foundation has been providing free of cost eye care facilities to the most deserving people under Al-Wahab Foundation’s Eye Care Project. Those who are referred for Eye Cataract Surgeries after examination at Eye Camps, are then operated without any charges at Al-Baseer Hospital. During his visit, Chairman Mufti Abdul Wahab engaged with the 40 patients being operated on and reviewed arrangements while expressing gratitude for the dedication of the team for this project. </p>
    </div>
</div>

